{"lemma":"مُشَيَّدَةٍ","slug":"مُشَيَّدَةٍ","root":"ش.#.د","root_slug":"ش-_-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُشَيَّدَةٍ","root":"شيد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23494","n23495"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23494","headword_ar":"مَشِيدٌ","root":"$yd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Plastered with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyd","text_ar":"شِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so, as some say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ay~adN","text_ar":"مُشَيَّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"built with gypsum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$yd","text_ar":"شيد"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gypsum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so, some say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ay~adN","text_ar":"مُشَيَّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raised high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made lofty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, S, A, K;) and so the former, applied to a place, (A,) or building: (TA:) the former has this meaning in the Kur xxii. 44: (Jel:) J says in the S, Ks says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iydN","text_ar":"مَشِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a sing., from the saying in the Kur, [ubi suprà,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaSorK ma$iydK","text_ar":"وَقَصْرٍ مَشِيدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ay~adN","text_ar":"مُشَيَّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a pl., from the saying in the same, [iv. 80,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY buruwjK mu$ay~adapK","text_ar":"فِى بُرُوجٍ مُشَيَّدَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this is a mistake: what Ks says is that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ay~adapN","text_ar":"مُشَيَّدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and teshdeed, is a pl. [i. e. a lexicological, not a grammatical, pl.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ay~adN","text_ar":"مُشَيَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB, K: *) or the saying of Ks [if as quoted in the S] may be expl. accord. to the opinion of those who hold that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iydN","text_ar":"مَشِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$ay~adN","text_ar":"مُشَيَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plastered with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyd","text_ar":"شِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":", on the supposition that the Arabs did not use"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iydapN","text_ar":"مَشِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as applied to a pl., but only to a sing.: (Az, L:) [for] Fr says that the pass. part. n. of the unaugmented verb only is used when applied to a sing. and not denoting repetition, or muchness; but either this or the pass. part. n. of the verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faE~ala","text_ar":"فَعَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used when applied to a sing. and denoting repetition, or muchness, and when applied to a pl.: thus you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabo$N ma*obuwHN","text_ar":"كَبْشٌ مَذْبُوحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ a slaughtered ram ”]; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ab~aHN","text_ar":"مُذَبَّحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but you may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxar~aqN","text_ar":"مُخَرَّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning “ a garment in which holes have been repeatedly made, ” or “ in which many holes have been made, ” or “ much pierced with holes, ” as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN maxoruwqN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ مَخْرُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ a garment in which a hole has been made, ” or “ in which holes have been made, ”] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibaA$N mu*ab~aHapN","text_ar":"كِبَاشٌ مُذَبَّحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ slaughtered rams ”]: and hence you may say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSorN mu$ay~adN","text_ar":"قَصْرٌ مُشَيَّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$oyiydN","text_ar":"تَشْيِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"denotes building, and the act of building is repeated, and a building becomes high by degrees. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","S","A","K","TA","Jel","Az","L"]},{"entry_id":"n23495","headword_ar":"مُشَيَّدٌ","root":"$yd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}